1. Script Basics
Start scripts with a shebang:
#!/bin/bash
Save as .sh
Make executable:
chmod +x script.sh

2. Running Scripts
./script.sh        # runs executable in current dir
bash script.sh     # runs via bash explicitly
sh script.sh       # may use a different shell

3. Variables
name="value"        # no spaces around =
echo $name
echo ${name}        # clearer, safer

Variable Types
greeting="hello"
count=42
fruits=(apple banana orange)

4. User Input
read variable
read -p "Enter name: " name

5. Script Parameters
$0 – script name
$1 $2 $3 – positional parameters
$@ – all parameters
$# – number of parameters

6. Arithmetic
result=$((5 + 3))
area=$((length * width))


Operators: + - * / % ++

7. Conditionals
if [ condition ]; then
  command
elif [ condition ]; then
  command
else
  command
fi

Numeric Comparisons
-eq -ne -lt -gt -le -ge
String Comparisons
== != -z -n

File Tests
-f file exists
-d directory exists
-r readable
-w writable
-x executable

Logical Operators
[[ cond1 && cond2 ]]
[[ cond1 || cond2 ]]
! condition

8. Loops
While Loop
while [ condition ]; do
  command
done

For Loops
for i in {1..5}; do
  command
done

for item in "${array[@]}"; do
  command
done

for ((i=1; i<=5; i++)); do
  command
done

Loop Control

break – exit loop

continue – skip iteration

9. Functions
my_function() {
  local var="$1"
  echo "$var"
}


Call with: my_function value

Access params with $1, $2

local limits scope to function

Return Codes
return 0   # success
return 1   # failure


Check with:

echo $?

10. Error Handling
$?          # exit status of last command
set -e      # exit on error
set -u      # exit on unset variables
set -x      # debug (print commands)
set +x      # disable debug


Best practice:

set -eux

11. Environment Variables
Common variables:
$HOME
$USER
$PATH
$SHELL
export VAR=value

12. File Operations
Read files line by line
Write with > (overwrite) and >> (append)
Test file properties before operating on them

13. Input Validation
Validate user input before use
Handle empty or invalid values
Fail safely with meaningful errors

